    "content" : "<div class=\"inline-attachment\"> \n <dl class=\"thumbnail\"> \n  <dt>\n   <a href=\"./download/file.php?id=34101&amp;sid=8a4c604a661ffa06a63b361233079fdb&amp;mode=view\"><img src=\"./download/file.php?id=34101&amp;t=1&amp;sid=8a4c604a661ffa06a63b361233079fdb\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"IMG_5856.jpg\" title=\"IMG_5856.jpg (242.83 KiB) Viewed 1908 times\"></a>\n  </dt> \n </dl> \n</div>Basically made my own, fabricated the trans-axle end and used a Porsche 996 cable shifter (around $75) not pretty but plan on covering it with a aluminum cowling.\n<div class=\"inline-attachment\"> \n <dl class=\"thumbnail\"> \n  <dt>\n   <a href=\"./download/file.php?id=34102&amp;sid=8a4c604a661ffa06a63b361233079fdb&amp;mode=view\"><img src=\"./download/file.php?id=34102&amp;t=1&amp;sid=8a4c604a661ffa06a63b361233079fdb\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"IMG_5857.jpg\" title=\"IMG_5857.jpg (262.47 KiB) Viewed 1908 times\"></a>\n  </dt> \n </dl> \n</div>\n<div class=\"inline-attachment\"> \n <dl class=\"thumbnail\"> \n  <dt>\n   <a href=\"./download/file.php?id=34103&amp;sid=8a4c604a661ffa06a63b361233079fdb&amp;mode=view\"><img src=\"./download/file.php?id=34103&amp;t=1&amp;sid=8a4c604a661ffa06a63b361233079fdb\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"IMG_6112.jpg\" title=\"IMG_6112.jpg (229.4 KiB) Viewed 1908 times\"></a>\n  </dt> \n </dl> \n</div> depending on how low you plan to go there may be room for a coil-over shock without the pivot mounting, I have a 15\" shock with 5\" of travel under the seat pan, though with your front drive shafts am guessing the issue is room front to back.\n<br> Stephen",
