    "content" : "So yesterday and today was all about the front chassis arms and trying to work out where they need to be in relation to the cab floor. Normally this would be easy as you would refer to your bus and take the measurements. Unfortunately for me my bus has already been 'renovated' which from what i can see was done like this - \n<br> Welder in Country B on phone to Bus owner in Country A - \"whats this bus meant to look like when i have finished\"?\n<br> Owner - 'I will send you over some photos'\n<br> Welder - ' Have not got internet, just describe it and i will have a go...........'\n<br> \n<br> Thats about it really. Reminds me of this advert - \n<a href=\"https://youtu.be/No26JKQKZNE\" class=\"postlink\">https://youtu.be/No26JKQKZNE</a>\n<br> \n<br> Anyway this is where we have got to - \n<br> \n<br> \n<a href=\"https://flic.kr/p/24Z5xcz\" class=\"postlink\"><img src=\"https://live.staticflickr.com/65535/40683688523_165718013a_k.jpg\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"Image\"></a>\n<a href=\"https://flic.kr/p/24Z5xcz\" class=\"postlink\">Front chassis arms</a> by \n<a href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/78596025@N06/\" class=\"postlink\">Duke of Boots1966</a>, on Flickr\n<br> \n<br> \n<a href=\"https://flic.kr/p/Tsoh1N\" class=\"postlink\"><img src=\"https://live.staticflickr.com/65535/33772770398_4396ef020d_k.jpg\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"Image\"></a>\n<a href=\"https://flic.kr/p/Tsoh1N\" class=\"postlink\">Front chassis arms</a> by \n<a href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/78596025@N06/\" class=\"postlink\">Duke of Boots1966</a>, on Flickr\n<br> \n<br> \n<a href=\"https://flic.kr/p/24Z5xfR\" class=\"postlink\"><img src=\"https://live.staticflickr.com/65535/40683688713_2dae3d020a_k.jpg\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"Image\"></a>\n<a href=\"https://flic.kr/p/24Z5xfR\" class=\"postlink\">Front chassis arms</a> by \n<a href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/78596025@N06/\" class=\"postlink\">Duke of Boots1966</a>, on Flickr\n<br> \n<br> \n<a href=\"https://flic.kr/p/2ecMcnR\" class=\"postlink\"><img src=\"https://live.staticflickr.com/65535/46734630295_d414326f21_z.jpg\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"Image\"></a>\n<a href=\"https://flic.kr/p/2ecMcnR\" class=\"postlink\">Front chassis arms</a> by \n<a href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/78596025@N06/\" class=\"postlink\">Duke of Boots1966</a>, on Flickr\n<br> \n<br> Even the 964 steering rack fits albeit swung through 180 degrees and a small amount of alloy cutting and tiging to be done to get it fixed in\n<br> \n<br> \n<a href=\"https://flic.kr/p/Tsoh4d\" class=\"postlink\"><img src=\"https://live.staticflickr.com/65535/33772770538_44837305a6_k.jpg\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"Image\"></a>\n<a href=\"https://flic.kr/p/Tsoh4d\" class=\"postlink\">Front chassis arms</a> by \n<a href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/78596025@N06/\" class=\"postlink\">Duke of Boots1966</a>, on Flickr\n<br> \n<br> Offered up the inner leg panels and the tool box. This is going to be the tricky bit because as mentioned above my bus is bucking VW dimension convention!\n<br> \n<br> \n<a href=\"https://flic.kr/p/2edJMUB\" class=\"postlink\"><img src=\"https://live.staticflickr.com/65535/46745477615_746b20f6cd_k.jpg\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"Image\"></a>\n<a href=\"https://flic.kr/p/2edJMUB\" class=\"postlink\">Garage phot</a> by \n<a href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/78596025@N06/\" class=\"postlink\">Duke of Boots1966</a>, on Flickr\n<br> \n<br> Gratuitous peeking out of garage shot\n<br> \n<br> \n<a href=\"https://flic.kr/p/2edJMYz\" class=\"postlink\"><img src=\"https://live.staticflickr.com/65535/46745477845_e5d63bf02f_k.jpg\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"Image\"></a>\n<a href=\"https://flic.kr/p/2edJMYz\" class=\"postlink\">Garage phot</a> by \n<a href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/78596025@N06/\" class=\"postlink\">Duke of Boots1966</a>, on Flickr",
    "lastEdited" : "Sun Apr 21, 2019 7:23 pm"
